-- Argentine bonds jump on prospect of talks with holdouts
-- By Jorge Otaola
-- Wed Jun 18, 2014 03:06PM EDT
-- None



BUENOS AIRES, June 18 (Reuters) - Argentina's over-the-counter bonds reversed losses on Wednesday, with the 2038 Par bonds shooting up 6 percent, after a lawyer representing the country in its bond dispute said it would negotiate with holdout investors next week.

